Some years ago.
I found an easy design exercise
that helps people understand and solve complex problems
and like other design exercises, it appears simple,
but under deep inspection
it reveals unexpected truths
about how we interact and understand things.
The task has 3 parts
and starts with something everyone can do
how to make toast.
It starts with paper and a marker
and without words, you draw how to make toast.
Most people draw this
They draw a loaf of bread, which is slicked, then put into a toaster.
The toast sits for a while.
It pops up. After two minutes, toast and happiness.
Over time I've collected hundreds of these drawings
and some are very good,
because they show the toast process quite clearly.
and some are not good.
