We're at tipping point in human history,
poised between gaining the stars and losing the Earth.
We've expanded greatly in recent years
our knowledge of how Earth fits in the universe.
NASA's Kepler mission has discovered
thousands of potential planets around other stars,
showing that Earth is one of billions in our galaxy
Kepler is telescope
that measures the subtle dimming of stars as planets pass in front of them,
blocking light from reaching us.
Kepler's info shows planet's sizes
distance between their parent star.
Together, this helps us understand whether planets are small and rocky,
like the terrestrial planets in our Solar System,
how much light they receive from parent sun.
